        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> I've gotten a little bored in Burning Woods but still want to get more of my Kunark drop spells (I have all the normal stuff through 53, excepting Convergence) so I decided to take a look at Skyfire.</P><P>So far, I haven't had too much trouble killing anything in there either root-dotting or fear kiting.  However, I have not found a great spot to fear kite in.  I've been pulling to the west wall near the BW zone, both north and south of it.  Each time, when feared, the mob will turn north and run, but just enough to the east that it paths out into the area where other mobs are.</P><P>So, my question is:  is there a good spot to pull to and fear where the mob won't path near other things?  Landmarks are good, coordinates are better.  =)</P><P>Thanks,</P><P>Ulzat,<BR>Heretic of Quellios</P><P> </font></td>
